text:
Yankees’ Masahiro Tanaka was released from the hospital after taking a line drive to head from Giancarlo Stanton.

"He went through a battery of tests at the hospital. Everything checked out well,” Yankees manager Aaron Boone announced.

name: NYDailyNews
text:
In a fiery Fourth of July speech, President Trump demonized protesters, China and the media.

The speech wasn’t as fiery as Trump's Mount Rushmore speech, when he said protesters were engaged in a “merciless campaign to wipe out our history.”
https://t.co/MuxMWVqNRU

name: NYDailyNews
text:
A rare, brain-eating amoeba infected a person in Florida.

The freshwater, single-cell amoeba, called Naegleria fowleri, has infected only 143 Americans in about 50 years. Only four of those people survived.
https://t.co/JR6MjCtIPs

name: NYDailyNews
text:
North Korea reiterated the Trump administration remains in its doghouse and that it has no interest in picking up nuclear negotiations.

“We do not feel any need to sit face to face with the U.S.,” North Korean Vice Foreign Minister Choe Son Hui said.
